le_df =
  le_df %>% 
  mutate(bc_le = (le)^1.5)

health_bc = lm(bc_le ~ polio_high + total_exp + diphtheria_low + hiv_aids + thin_1_19, data = le_df)

Identify influentical observations

plot(health_bc, which = 5)

# Identify influential observations using Cook's distance
cutoff <- 4/nrow(le_df)
plot(health_bc, which = 4, cook.levels = cutoff)
abline(h = cutoff, lty = 2, col = "red")

cook = cooks.distance(health_bc)
influential_obs = as.numeric(names(cook)[(cook > cutoff)])

#define new data frame with influential points removed
no_influ_le = le_df[-influential_obs, ]

no_influ_health_bc = lm(bc_le ~ polio_high + total_exp + diphtheria_low + hiv_aids + thin_1_19, data = no_influ_le)
summary(no_influ_health_bc)

Model Validation

set.seed(1)

# Use 5-fold validation and create the training sets
train = trainControl(method = "cv", number = 5)

# Fit the 4-variables model
model = train(bc_le ~ polio_high + total_exp + diphtheria_low + hiv_aids + thin_1_19, data = no_influ_le, trControl = train, method = 'lm', na.action = na.pass)

model$finalModel
